  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your<strong> chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air, then boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>diced chicken thigh</strong> and cook for 4-5 min on each side or until lightly browned</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1678302184791-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1678302184791-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1678302184791-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1678302184791-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1678302184791-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the chicken is cooking, peel and finely dice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>sweet potato[es]</strong> into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Trim, then chop your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong> into quarters</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1678302191849-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1678302191849-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1678302191849-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1678302191849-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1678302191849-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is lightly browned, reduce the heat to medium-high</p><p>Add the <strong>diced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until slightly softened</p><p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong>, <strong>creamed coconut</strong> and <strong>red Thai curry paste</strong> in 300ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [390ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>red</strong> <strong>Thai-style stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1678302196644-x200.jpg",
